-- Senators Snap Rangers’ Five-Game Winning Streak in NHL With 3-0 Shutout
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-13T05:02:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/senators-snap-rangers-five-game-winning-streak-in-nhl-with-3-0-shutout.html
Jason Spezza scored two goals as the
 Ottawa Senators  won 3-0 to snap the New York Rangers’ five-game
winning streak in the National Hockey League.  Spezza scored the opening goal 8 minutes, 54 seconds into
the second period last night at New York’s Madison Square
Garden.  Milan Michalek added a goal with six minutes left in the
final period and Spezza scored his second goal about 90 seconds
later. Goalie Craig Anderson had 34 saves for the Senators.  The Rangers are atop the five-team Eastern Conference’s
Atlantic Division. The Senators are second in the conference’s
Northeast Division behind the  Boston Bruins .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
